<subSubSection id="C36760EEFFEADE2BD835DF72FBF7FC82" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC23365FFEADE2BD835DF72FBF7FC82" blockId="9.[264,1323,625,771]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
The original description states ‘Reared from blackberry gall, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D48E6FFEADE2BDADDDF72FAC6FD0B" box="[992,1322,625,650]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Diastrophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cuscutaeformis">
<emphasis id="B909EF77FFEADE2BDADDDF72FAC6FD0B" box="[992,1322,625,650]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Diastrophus cuscutaeformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
O.S.’ All known species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D48E6FFEADE2BDB66DF9AFCEDFD33" box="[603,769,665,690]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Agrostocynips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B909EF77FFEADE2BDB66DF9AFCEDFD33" box="[603,769,665,690]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Agrostocynips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are leaf­miner parasitoids (
<taxonomicName id="4C7D48E6FFEADE2BDD75DF9AFB4AFD32" box="[1096,1190,665,691]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Diptera</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D48E6FFEADE2BDD8FDF9AFED1FD5A" authorityName="Buffington" authorityYear="2004" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Agromyzidae</taxonomicName>
); it is probable the described specimens (
<typeStatus id="54C68DC7FFEADE2BDA14DFC2FC7DFD5A" box="[809,913,705,731]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus id="54C68DC7FFEADE2BDAF3DFC2FBD9FD5A" box="[974,1077,705,731]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">paratype</typeStatus>
) emerged from leafminers accompanying the vegetation in which the gall was formed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
